IoT-Based Fire Detection System
Problem Statement:
Fire accidents cause major property loss due to lack of early
warnings in homes and small offices.
Objective:
Develop a fire detection system using gas and temperature
sensors that alert users with buzzer and mobile notifications.
Requirements:
Arduino Uno or NodeMCU
MQ-2 Gas/Smoke Sensor
DHT11 Temperature Sensor
Buzzer
LEDs
Blynk or IFTTT for phone alerts
Expected Outcome:
A prototype that activates local alarms and sends alerts to the
user’s phone when fire or gas is detected.

